translated: Eldh, Sven Alexander, second city physician, Skara, born January 8, 1899 in Lidköp to Anders Gustaf E. and Hanna Carlsson. Married on May 29, Iris Anna Maria Bärg. Children: Ulla born in 1937. Studied and passed exams in Skara in 1918, obtained a medical bachelor's degree in Uppsala in 1923 and a medical licentiate in 1928. Worked as a medical intern at Sätra brunn from 1924 to 1926 and in 1928, as an extra assistant physician at the pathology department in Uppsala in 1925 and 1926, as an assistant and acting assistant physician at the chest clinic in Uppsala from 1927 to 1928, as an assistant physician at the medical department there from 1928 to 1929, and as a practicing physician in Skara since 1929. Also held positions as second city physician and physician at Skara hospital since 1931, physician at Trollhätte power plant and post physician in Skara since 1931. He was a member of the city council (socialist) since 1931, vice chairman of the health committee, and a member of the child welfare committee and the pension committee.
